Part of a busy beach in Cornwall has been cordoned off after a section of cliff collapsed, causing rocks to fall on to the sands.Cornwall Council said part of Great Western beach in Newquay has been closed, and warned people to "stay away from the area".It said it now planned to "carry out inspections" and "make the area safe". Great Western is a popular beach in central Newquay within walking distance of many hotels and guest houses, and is in an area of coastline vulnerable to cliff falls.
